title.rendered: San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023 live stream TV channel, music Schedule

content.rendered:
The San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023 will be held on Feb. 9-25 in San Antonio, Texas. At the 2023 Rodeo, catch 14 PRCA Rodeo performances followed by entertainment along with a Ranch Rodeo and Xtreme Bulls. Performances start at 7 p.m. Mondays-Saturdays and at 4 p.m. Sundays. Doors open two hours prior to each performance.

San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo
Venue Freeman Coliseum, San Antonio, Texas
Dates Feb. 9 – 25
Networks Cowboy Channel, Cowboy Channel +

Each action-packed Rodeo kicks off with the patriotic Grand Entry and features bareback riding, steer wrestling, team roping, saddle bronc riding, tie-down roping, barrel racing and bull riding. You don’t want to miss the specialty acts as well as mutton bustin’ and the calf scramble.

What TV Channel will the San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023 be on?

The entirety of the San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo’s main performances will air live on the The Cowboy Channel, Cowboy Channel + from Feb 9-25, 2023. portal-alpha.financial-ombudsman.org.uk has rounded up everything you need to know about how to watch the San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023 on TV and online.

How to watch San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023?

Western Lifestyle Network is pleased to share with an individual the latest and finest in rodeo news in addition to events, up next will be the highly-anticipated San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023! The SASSR will be televised Feb 10-26, 2022 and performances live on The Cowboy Channel and Cowboy Channel +. The Cowboy Channel now available on Dish Network-232, Direct TV-603, Cox-260 anytime, and anywhere.

The Cowboy Channel:

  1. AT&T (Channel 566)
  2. Charter Spectrum
  3. Comcast
  4. Suddenlink
  5. Sling TV’s Heartland Package
  6. Verizon FiOS TV

To find out if RFD-TV and THE COWBOY CHANNEL are available in your area, please click here and enter your zip code also choose your Pay TV provider.

Cowboy Channel +

Stream The Cowboy Channel programming live, watch past episodes of your favorite shows, and follow all the latest rodeo action. The Cowboy Channel Plus is available for only $9.99 a month or save up to 25% and purchase the whole year for $89.99. To sign up for the PRCA on The Cowboy Channel Plus app, visit www.cowboychannelplus.com.

Supported Device

  • Web: Any web-connected desktop, laptop, tablet, or mobile phone using the latest version of Chrome (recommended), Firefox, Safari, Edge, or Internet Explorer.
  • Mobile App: If you have an iPhone or iPad, search for “Cowboy Channel +” in the App Store.
  • TV: If you have an Apple TV (4th generation) or Roku, search for “Cowboy Channel +” in the App Store or in the Roku Channel Store.

San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023 format

At the 2023 Rodeo, catch 19 PRCA Rodeo performances followed by entertainment along with a Ranch Rodeo and Xtreme Bulls. Performances start at 7 p.m. Mondays-Saturdays and at 4 p.m. Sundays. Doors open two hours prior to each performance. Each action-packed Rodeo kicks off with the patriotic Grand Entry and features bareback riding, steer wrestling, team roping, saddle bronc riding, tie-down roping, barrel racing and bull riding. You don’t want to miss the specialty acts as well as mutton bustin’ and the charreada.

Rodeo Wildcard

On Friday, February 25, the 10 contestants in each event who did not advance to the Finals from the Semifinal will have one more chance to make it into the Finals. The highest score and fastest time wins!

Who Competes at the Rodeo?

The San Antonio Rodeo is sanctioned by the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA) and the Women’s Professional Rodeo Association (WPRA).

The PRCA and WPRA rodeo seasons begin on October 1 and end September 30 each year.

Contestants are eligible to enter based on the below criteria:

PRCA

  • Top 45 contestants in each event in the 2022 PRCA World Standings
  • Top 5 contestants in each event in the 2023 PRCA World Standings

WPRA

  • Top 4 contestants from 2023 WPRA Pro Rodeo Standings
  • Top 32 from 2022 Pro Rodeo Standings
  • Top 4 from the 2022 WPRA Tour Standings
  • Top 10 contestants from the San Antonio Rodeo Qualifier

WPRA Breakaway Roping

  • Top 10 contestants from 2023 WPRA Breakaway Roping World Standings
  • Top 40 from 2022 WPRA Pro Rodeo Breakaway World Standings

San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo 2023 live music lineup

Luckily for the audience, entertainment doesn’t end when the rodeo is finished! After each rodeo performance, an award-winning artist will take the stage. Some of the artists performing at this year’s San Antonio Stock Show & Rodeo include Ryan Bingham, Jake Owen, Midland, Carly Pearce and more.
